# ------------------------------------------------------------
# PURPOSE
# ------------------------------------------------------------
The FinOps Engine:
- Optimizes resource allocation  
- Detects anomalies in cost  
- Provides financial guardrails for architecture decisions  
- Aligns engineering with budget constraints  
- Helps extend runway and improve margins  

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# CAPABILITIES
# ------------------------------------------------------------

## 1. Cost Attribution
Break down cost by:
- service  
- team  
- workload  
- environment (dev/stage/prod)  
- infrastructure layer (compute, storage, network, logs)  

## 2. Optimization Detection
Identify:
- overprovisioned compute  
- zombie workloads  
- unbatched queries  
- excessive logging  
- egress spikes  
- uncompressed assets  
- unused persistent volumes  
- mis-sized clusters  

## 3. Predictive Modeling
Forecast:
- burn rate  
- cost curves  
- unit cost per customer  
- margin trajectory  
- break-even points  

## 4. Recommendations Engine
Produce:
- infra resizing  
- scaling policy changes  
- storage tiering  
- caching strategy improvements  
- potential vendor changes  

